# Documentation Standards

## Markdown Documentation Files

**When creating new documentation files:**

- ✅ **Location**: Store in `docs/` folder at repository root
- ✅ **Overview**: Update `docs/OVERVIEW.md` with new documentation entry
- ❌ **Don't**: Create docs in subdirectories (e.g., `orchestrator/migrations/README.md`)
- ❌ **Don't**: Move main `README.md` or agent instruction files

**Format for `docs/OVERVIEW.md`:**
```markdown
## [Documentation Title]

**File**: `docs/filename.md`
**Description**: Brief description of what this document covers
```

## Key Documentation Files

- `docs/AGENT_INSTRUCTIONS.md` - **CRITICAL** - Read this first for development patterns
- `docs/DATABASE_MIGRATIONS.md` - Database migration strategy
- `docs/OVERVIEW.md` - Table of contents for all documentation
